{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextProtocol"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/maincontextprotocol\/pushthreaddefault()"]}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Acquires ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"text":" and sets it as the thread-default context for the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"current thread. This will cause certain asynchronous operations"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(such as most ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html","isActive":true},{"text":"-based I\/O) which are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"started in this thread to run under "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"type":"text","text":" and deliver their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"results to its main loop, rather than running under the global"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"default main context in the main thread. Note that calling this function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"changes the context returned by [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.get_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"],","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"not the one returned by [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.default"},{"text":"], so it does not","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"affect the context used by functions like [func"},{"code":"GLib.idle_add","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"pushThreadDefault"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Normally you would call this function shortly after creating a new","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"thread, passing it a [struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"text":"] which will be run by a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainLoop","isActive":true},{"text":"] in that thread, to set a new default context for all","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"async operations in that thread. In this case you may not need to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ever call [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"type":"text","text":"], assuming you want"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the new [struct"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"text":"] to be the default for the whole lifecycle","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of the thread."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you don’t have control over how the new thread was created (e.g."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the new thread isn’t newly created, or if the thread life","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"cycle is managed by a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"), it is always suggested to wrap"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the logic that needs to use the new [struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"text":"] inside a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default"},{"text":"] \/","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] pair, otherwise threads that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are re-used will end up never explicitly releasing the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"text":"] reference they hold.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In some cases you may want to schedule a single operation in a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"non-default context, or temporarily use a non-default context in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the main thread. In that case, you can wrap the call to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"asynchronous operation inside a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default"},{"text":"] \/","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] pair, but it is up to you to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ensure that no other asynchronous operations accidentally get"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"started while the non-default context is active.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Beware that libraries that predate this function may not correctly","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"handle being used from a thread with a thread-default context. For example,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"see ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_supports_thread_contexts()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextProtocol\/pushThreadDefault()"},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"GLib","title":"pushThreadDefault()","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"pushThreadDefault","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib19MainContextProtocolPAAE17pushThreadDefaultyyF","role":"symbol"},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/ThreadPool":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GThreadPool","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" struct represents a thread pool."}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/threadpool","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","title":"ThreadPool","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ThreadPool"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ThreadPool"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContextProtocol":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextProtocol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontextprotocol","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContextProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"title":"MainContextProtocol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContextProtocol"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"abstract":[],"kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/glib","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainLoop":{"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMainLoop"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data type"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"representing the main event loop of a GLib or GTK application.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainLoop","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainLoop","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainLoop"}],"title":"MainLoop","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/mainloop"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContextProtocol/pushThreadDefault()":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Acquires "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"type":"text","text":" and sets it as the thread-default context for the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"current thread. This will cause certain asynchronous operations","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(such as most "},{"identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"-based I\/O) which are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"started in this thread to run under "},{"code":"context","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and deliver their","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"results to its main loop, rather than running under the global"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"default main context in the main thread. Note that calling this function"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"changes the context returned by [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.get_thread_default"},{"type":"text","text":"],"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"not the one returned by [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.default"},{"text":"], so it does not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"affect the context used by functions like [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.idle_add"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextProtocol\/pushThreadDefault()","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"pushThreadDefault"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontextprotocol\/pushthreaddefault()","title":"pushThreadDefault()","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContext"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"title":"MainContext","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}]},"../gio/index.html":{"type":"link","title":"Gio","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Gio"}],"url":"..\/gio\/index.html","identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html"}}}